Analysis of MSHA Inspections, Violations, and Accident Data

An open and ongoing analysis of the data provided by the US Mine Safety & Health Administration. See github.com/mwfrost/MSHA for details.

This script uses rmongodb to write the flat files to mongo collections, and uses RMongo to read them.

rmongodb

Write each source table to a mongodb collection


data.frame.to.mongo <- function(df, db, col, fields = names(df)) {
    mongo <- mongo.create()
    if (mongo.is.connected(mongo)) {
        for (i in 1:nrow(df)) {
            b <- mongo.bson.from.list(df[i, fields])
            # print(b) print('----------------')
            if (!is.null(b)) {
                mongo.insert(mongo, paste(db, col, sep = "."), b)
            } else {
                print("NULL BSON object")
                print(t(df[i, ]))
            }
        }
    }
}



fields <- setdiff(names(mdat), "DIRECTIONS_TO_MINE")
# data.frame.to.mongo(mdat, 'msha', 'mines', fields)

Now switch to the RMongo library and check the data. Some sample Mongo aggregations on the Mines collection, based on these examples:

http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/reference/sql-aggregation-comparison/

http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/reference/sql-comparison/

Example mongodb search: db.mines.find({MINE_ID : 1519137})


mongo <- mongoDbConnect(dbName = "msha", host = "localhost", port = "27017")

output <- dbAggregate(mongo, "mines", c("{ \n                         $match: { NO_EMPLOYEES: {$gt: 0} } \n                         }", 
    "{ \n                         $group: { \n                         _id: \"$PRIMARY_SIC\", \n                         employees : {$sum:\"$NO_EMPLOYEES\"}\n                         } \n                         }"))

print(output)

Compare the time it takes to run a simple aggregation in mongo to the same task with ddply()

mongo <- mongoDbConnect(dbName = "msha", host = "localhost", port = "27017")

system.time(dbAggregate(mongo, "mines", c("{ $match: { NO_EMPLOYEES: {$gt: 0} } }", 
    "{ $group: { _id: \"$PRIMARY_SIC\", employees : {$sum:\"$NO_EMPLOYEES\"}} }")))

##    user  system elapsed 
##   0.041   0.001   0.212



system.time(ddply(mdat[mdat$NO_EMPLOYEES > 0, ], .(PRIMARY_SIC), summarize, 
    employees = sum(NO_EMPLOYEES)))

##    user  system elapsed 
##   0.019   0.001   0.020

Evantually add some utility functions

Inspections

Inspections.txt is too long to store in memory in R, so read pieces of it and load those into mongo.

skip_count <- 250000
start_row <- skip_count + 1

idat <- read.table("./data/msha_source/Inspections.TXT", nrows = skip_count, 
    header = T, sep = "|", fill = T, quote = "\"", comment.char = "")

## Warning: invalid input found on input connection
## './data/msha_source/Inspections.TXT' Warning: EOF within quoted string

inames <- names(idat)

while (start_row < 2e+06) {
    print(paste("About to scan records ", start_row, " through ", start_row + 
        skip_count))

    idat_temp <- read.table("./data/msha_source/Inspections.TXT", nrows = skip_count, 
        header = F, sep = "|", fill = T, skip = start_row, quote = "\"", comment.char = "")
    names(idat_temp) <- inames
    print(paste("Rows collected: ", nrow(idat)))

    # data.frame.to.mongo(idat_temp, 'msha', 'inspections', inames)


    start_row <- start_row + skip_count
}

## [1] "About to scan records  250001  through  500001"

## Warning: invalid input found on input connection
## './data/msha_source/Inspections.TXT' Warning: incomplete final line found
## on './data/msha_source/Inspections.TXT'

## Error: no lines available in input


mongo1 <- mongo.create()
mongo.count(mongo1, "msha.inspections", query = mongo.bson.empty())

## [1] 66564

Compare the operation time


system.time(dbAggregate(mongo, "inspections", c("{ $match: { CURRENT_CONTROLLER_NAME: \"CONSOL Energy Inc\" } }", 
    "{ $group: { _id: \"$CURRENT_MINE_NAME\", inspections : {$sum:1}} }")))

##    user  system elapsed 
##   0.046   0.000   0.539


system.time(ddply(subset(idat, CURRENT_CONTROLLER_NAME == "CONSOL Energy Inc"), 
    .(CURRENT_MINE_NAME), nrow))

## Error: object 'CURRENT_CONTROLLER_NAME' not found

Violations

skip_count <- 250000
start_row <- skip_count + 1

vdat <- read.table("./data/msha_source/Violations.TXT", nrows = skip_count, 
    header = T, sep = "|", fill = T, as.is = c(1:55), quote = "\"", comment.char = "")
vnames <- names(vdat)

while (start_row < 2e+06) {
    print(paste("About to scan records ", start_row, " through ", start_row + 
        skip_count))

    vdat_temp <- read.table("./data/msha_source/Violations.TXT", nrows = skip_count, 
        header = F, sep = "|", fill = T, as.is = c(1:55), skip = start_row, 
        quote = "", comment.char = "")
    names(vdat_temp) <- vnames

    # data.frame.to.mongo(vdat_temp, 'msha', 'violations')

    print(paste("Rows collected: ", nrow(vdat)))
    # print(paste('Events ', vdat[last_row,c('EVENT_NO')] , ' through ' ,
    # vdat[nrow(vdat),c('EVENT_NO')]))
    start_row <- start_row + skip_count
    # last_row <- nrow(vdat)
}
